Entry 1: Descent

The Crucible is not simply a place. It is verdict at it's purest. Judgment. The chains broke through only after I embraced my guilt, yet the path that lies ahead was darker still. Whoever is reading this, realize this: there is no escape. Only eternal torment. They are always listening.

Entry 2: The First Trial

They asked what I truly feared most. I did not tell the truth. They walls shifted their position, the trials transformed. The Crucible does not tolerate deception.

Entry 3: Deception

Today I met another one like me. I am starting to forget who I am. I don't know my name anymore. I am starting to turn to insanity. The man I met wore my face. Stated my regrets. I brutally slashed him. The wound bloomed on my own chest. The crucible is not a force to be reckoned with. It crafts enemies from your memories.

The Labryinth:

The labyrinth alters not by stone, but by judgement. Stay proud, and the path will narrow. Lie, and face your end. Encourage rightness, and find your escape.

Scratched Note:

Don't look them in the eyes. They know who you are. They whisper. They want you to break.

Ripped Parchment:

The bridge echoes. The river speaks your name. I answered. The river knows your voice....

Scrap:
The trials will never come to an end. They only adapt. Escape is just a rumor simply told by the hopeful to the hopeless.

Letter that was never sent:
If I ever die, know that my fighting wasn't for glory, but to atone for my sins. The day I die is the day I battle my sins in the underworld.

The Crucible:

We see you, Alex. You can run, but you can't hide. There is no escape. Because all you do is run. You're no knight. You're a coward. We will always be watching you.








